  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mexico Earthquake Relief Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On Sept. 19, 2017, Mexico City and surroundings, including Morelos and Puebla, suffered devastation from a 7.1M earthquake. Hundreds were killed and countless homes, schools, and community buildings were destroyed. This followed an 8.1M quake in Oaxaca and Chiapas on Sept. 7. This fund was created to provide immediate relief to survivors in the form of food, shelter, water, and medicine. In addition, it is now supporting longer-term assistance to help residents recover and rebuild.</narrative>
  </description>
